<HEADLINE>
<P>
POVERTY FACTOR IN IMMIGRATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Father Boyle expressed the economic and social tragedy facing millions of 
Mexican and South American immigrants. 
</P>
<P>
And the good father is right -- it is our duty to help out the less fortunate. 
But the Catholic Church's generous offer of U.S. tax dollars isn't going to 
solve the problem. Modern birth control will solve the problem. If women used 
their God-given intelligence and reproduced responsibly, a great deal of 
poverty would be eradicated. 
</P>
<P>
PAMELA CANDELORE 
</P>
<P>
Escondido 
</P>
</TEXT>
