MORNING REPORT: PEOPLE WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jerry Lewis Angered: Jerry Lewis has lashed out at a National Enquirer report 
that he will play a diminished role in the Muscular Dystrophy Telethon he has 
headed for 40 years. 
</P>
<P>
"I mean, come on, if you're gonna lie, at least make up something that has some 
meat to it," Lewis said. The paper reported that Lewis went "berserk" when 
informed that he had been stripped of his production duties and would be 
primarily the telethon's emcee. The story said the move was made in a January 
MDA board meeting because telethon ratings were slipping and contributions were 
not as high as expected. Lewis and MDA officials denied the claims. GREG 
BRAXTON 
