<TEXT>
<P>
The police officer who arrested North Carolina basketball player King Rice on 
assault charges and resisting arrest exploited the point guard's celebrity 
status, Coach Dean Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't know what his deal is," Smith told the Chapel Hill (N.C.) Newspaper 
Wednesday. "I hear (the officer) used to follow J.R. (Reid) around, too." Reid 
is a former North Carolina basketball star playing in the NBA. 
</P>
<P>
Rice, 21, will appear in District Court May 31 to face charges he assaulted 
Natalie Nester, his girlfriend, a member of the North Carolina State women's 
team. 
