<TEXT>
<P>
BOMB BOOM: Setting bombs is becoming more popular in Orange County, and no one 
seems to know why. . . . In 1988, the sheriff's bomb squad handled 98 exploded 
and unexploded bombs, but last year the figure was 138, and this year is ahead 
of that pace. . . . The good news: Nearly half of the bombs never go off, most 
are directed against property, not people, and bombs have killed only three 
people since 1980 -- and one of them was the bomber. Jeffrey A. Perlman and 
Sonni Efron 
</P>
