<P>
VIDEO STORE ROBBED; OWNER TIED UP BY GUN-WIELDING MEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two robbers tied up a video store owner and threatened him with a shotgun 
Thursday while they stole an undetermined number of videotapes and $100 in 
cash, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The robbers walked into Odyssey Video at 16481 Springdale St. about 2:40 p.m. 
when no other customers were inside, locked the door and put up the closed 
sign, Police Lt. Roger Parker said. 
</P>
<P>
The pair tied up the owner, identified as Tuyen Thien Dao, 53, of Irvine, with 
a telephone cord and spent about 10 minutes ransacking the store, looking for 
money, Parker said. 
</P>
<P>
Dao was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
Both men were described as being Asian, about 5 feet, 3 inches tall and 
weighing about 115 pounds, with short black hair. One man was wearing a white 
glove on his left hand, and the other was wearing a black leather jacket, 
Parker said. 
