SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: FALLBROOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opponents of a proposed landfill on Aspen Road will hold a protest walk at the 
site, starting at 10 a.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Walks ranging from 100 yards to 3 miles -- around the perimeter of the proposed 
dump -- are planned, said Gib Lee, organizer of the protest. 
</P>
<P>
Opponents of the Aspen Road landfill say it would worsen the area's air quality 
and endanger the ground water, which is tapped by neighboring Camp Pendleton. 
</P>
<P>
The Aspen Road site is one of three being considered by county officials -- the 
others being in the Pauma Valley east of Interstate 15 and near Warner Springs 
-- to accommodate North County's trash as the existing landfill in San Marcos 
approaches capacity. 
</P>
