<P>
DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: VENTURA FREEWAY LANES TO BE CLOSED FOR WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Work on widening the Ventura Freeway will require nighttime lane closures this 
weekend in the west San Fernando Valley, the state Department of Transportation 
announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
From 10 p.m. today to 11 a.m. Saturday, up to three westbound lanes will be 
closed between White Oak and Wilbur avenues, Caltrans said. 
</P>
<P>
At the same time, up to three eastbound lanes will be closed between Winnetka 
and Lindley avenues. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the westbound White Oak on-ramp and Reseda Boulevard off-ramp will 
be closed during the same hours as will the eastbound Winnetka on-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
From 10 p.m. Saturday to 11 a.m. Sunday, up to three eastbound lanes will be 
closed between Winnetka and Lindley avenues, Caltrans officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the eastbound Vanalden Avenue on-ramp will be closed during those hours. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans is adding a fifth lane each way on the freeway from Topanga Canyon 
Boulevard to Universal City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
