<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saudis to Expand Oil Output Capacity: Saudi Arabia will soon start a 
multibillion-dollar oil production capacity expansion program aimed at keeping 
the kingdom the world's biggest oil exporter in the next century, industry 
sources said. Saudi Arabian Oil Co., or Saudi Aramco, is expected to award 
contracts in June for oil field facilities and equipment upgrading that will 
push its sustainable outut to around 10 million barrels per day in the next 10 
years from the current average of 6.5 million to 7 million barrels per day. The 
cost of the project is estimated to be somewhere between $12 billion and $15 
billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
