<P>
LONG BEACH MAN KILLED IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Long Beach man was killed today when his car slammed into a bridge in Buena 
Park, police said. 
</P>
<P>
William J. Baxter, 21, was pronounced dead at the scene after the accident at 
1:16 a.m., Buena Park Officer Rich McMillen said. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on Valley View Street south of Artesia Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Baxter, the lone occupant of the vehicle, drifted across a lane and rammed into 
a concrete section of a bridge spanning a flood control channel of Coyote 
Creek, police said. 
</P>
<P>
After crashing into the bridge, the car slammed into a light pole, McMillen 
said, adding that Baxter died from massive head and internal injuries. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation revealed that the Long Beach man was driving at a minimum 
speed of 65 m.p.h., police said. 
</P>
<P>
McMillen said an autopsy would seek to determine whether Baxter was driving 
under the influence of alcohol or drugs. 
</P>
