<P>
ACTON MAN HELD IN GUN BARRAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 43-year-old Acton man was arrested this morning following a two-hour standoff 
with Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies which began when the man shot at 
deputies, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
John Patrick Sass was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder at 4 a.m. and 
was being held without bail, Deputy Bill Wehner said. 
</P>
<P>
Two hours earlier, deputies arrived at Sass' home in the 5800 block of Hubbard 
Road after receiving reports of gunfire. As deputies approached the house, Sass 
fired several shots at them, Wehner said. No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies surrounded the house. After two hours of negotiating with Sass by 
telephone, the gunman surrendered, Wehner said. Deputies had not determined why 
Sass began firing his gun, he said. 
</P>
