</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WHEELING, W.Va. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. Gaston Caperton, whose messy divorce from his wife of 23 years made 
headlines last year, today announced his engagement to Wheeling Symphony 
conductor Rachael Worby. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a really special day for us," Caperton said at a news conference at 
Oglebay Park Amphitheater, where the orchestra appears during the summer. 
</P>
<P>
The announcement comes less than a year after the first-term Democratic 
governor and his wife, Dee, divorced and she sued him for fraud. 
</P>
<P>
After the divorce, Dee Caperton, a former House of Delegates member, ran for 
the Democratic nomination for state treasurer, saying she would be able to work 
cooperatively with her ex-husband. She was defeated in Tuesday's primary. 
</P>
<P>
Speculation that Caperton, 50, and Orby, 41, were romantically involved sprang 
up when they attended many public functions together, including a visit to the 
White House. 
</P>
