<TEXT>
<P>
A mother and her boyfriend were arrested on charges of neglect today after a 
smoky house fire that killed four of the woman's children and critically 
injured two others, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
An investigator said the fire may have been caused by children playing with 
matches. 
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out before 10 p.m. Thursday, trapping six of seven siblings left 
alone in their two-story downtown home, said police spokesman Lt. Roosevelt 
Harrell. 
</P>
<P>
An 11-year-old girl was helped to safety from a second-story window by a 
neighbor, Harrell said. 
</P>
<P>
Four girls -- Lashandra Moore, 5; Alexis Moses, 6; Jocelyn Moses, 8, and Daphne 
Moses, 9 -- died. Two brothers, Antonio Moore, 3, and Justine Moses, 2, were 
hospitalized in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old mother of the victims, whose name was not made public, was 
arrested on suspicion of neglect of children leading to death, Harrell said. 
The woman's 43-year-old boyfriend also was arrested on suspicion of child 
neglect. 
