THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
DOLEMAN NOW TOP-PAID VIKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MINNEAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Doleman has signed a contract that makes him the best-paid player in 
Minnesota Vikings' history and one of the NFL's best-paid defensive linemen, 
according to agents with knowledge of the agreement. 
</P>
<P>
The agents said Doleman's one-year contract is worth about $1.4 million, the 
Star Tribune reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The deal might be worth as much as $1.6 million including incentive clauses, 
the agents said. The agreement also includes money from an out-of-court 
settlement, the agents said. 
</P>
<P>
Doleman, an All-Pro defensive end, made $300,000 in base salary last season. 
</P>
<P>
If the estimates are correct, Doleman's contract would eclipse those of the 
highest-paid Vikings, quarterback Wade Wilson and running back Herschel Walker, 
both of whom will make more than $1 million for the 1990 season. 
</P>
